# alpha_01_parth

## Hypothesis
Analyst expectations (such as EPS estimates) provide forward-looking signals about a company’s future profitability.

A higher `est_eps / close` indicates that the stock is relatively undervalued compared to its expected earnings. By applying a time-series rank (`ts_rank`), we capture persistent strength in earnings expectations over time.

Using `group_rank` with industry neutralization ensures that companies are compared within similar business environments, removing structural biases across industries.

Therefore, stocks with relatively higher expected earnings compared to their price within the same industry are more likely to outperform.

---

## Alpha Expression
group_rank(ts_rank(est_eps/close, 60), industry)

